Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.NutritionProduct` for use in FHIR R4

0.0.1-snapshot-3
Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-NutritionProduct Version:
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-10 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionNutritionProduct

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element NutritionProduct for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Basic

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • Use this Extension: Cross-version Profile for R5.NutritionProduct for use in FHIR R4

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element NutritionProduct for use in FHIR R4.

  • code: CodeableConcept: The code assigned to the product, for example a USDA NDB number, a USDA FDC ID number, or a Langual code.
  • status: code: The current state of the product.
  • category: CodeableConcept: Nutrition products can have different classifications - according to its nutritional properties, preparation methods, etc.
  • manufacturer: Reference: The organisation (manufacturer, representative or legal authorization holder) that is responsible for the device.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • amount: Ratio: The amount of nutrient expressed in one or more units: X per pack / per serving / per dose.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • amount: Ratio: The amount of ingredient that is in the product.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • type: CodeableConcept: A code specifying which characteristic of the product is being described (for example, colour, shape).
  • value: CodeableConcept, string, Quantity, base64Binary, Attachment, boolean: The actual characteristic value corresponding to the type.
  • quantity: Quantity: The amount of items or instances that the resource considers, for instance when referring to 2 identical units together.
  • identifier: Identifier: The identifier for the physical instance, typically a serial number or manufacturer number.
  • name: string: The name for the specific product.
  • lotNumber: string: The identification of the batch or lot of the product.
  • expiry: dateTime: The time after which the product is no longer expected to be in proper condition, or its use is not advised or not allowed.
  • useBy: dateTime: The time after which the product is no longer expected to be in proper condition, or its use is not advised or not allowed.
  • biologicalSourceEvent: Identifier: An identifier that supports traceability to the event during which material in this product from one or more biological entities was obtained or pooled.
  • note: Annotation: Comments made about the product.

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element NutritionProduct for use in FHIR R4.

  • code: CodeableConcept: The code assigned to the product, for example a USDA NDB number, a USDA FDC ID number, or a Langual code.
  • status: code: The current state of the product.
  • category: CodeableConcept: Nutrition products can have different classifications - according to its nutritional properties, preparation methods, etc.
  • manufacturer: Reference: The organisation (manufacturer, representative or legal authorization holder) that is responsible for the device.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • amount: Ratio: The amount of nutrient expressed in one or more units: X per pack / per serving / per dose.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • amount: Ratio: The amount of ingredient that is in the product.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • type: CodeableConcept: A code specifying which characteristic of the product is being described (for example, colour, shape).
  • value: CodeableConcept, string, Quantity, base64Binary, Attachment, boolean: The actual characteristic value corresponding to the type.
  • quantity: Quantity: The amount of items or instances that the resource considers, for instance when referring to 2 identical units together.
  • identifier: Identifier: The identifier for the physical instance, typically a serial number or manufacturer number.
  • name: string: The name for the specific product.
  • lotNumber: string: The identification of the batch or lot of the product.
  • expiry: dateTime: The time after which the product is no longer expected to be in proper condition, or its use is not advised or not allowed.
  • useBy: dateTime: The time after which the product is no longer expected to be in proper condition, or its use is not advised or not allowed.
  • biologicalSourceEvent: Identifier: An identifier that supports traceability to the event during which material in this product from one or more biological entities was obtained or pooled.
  • note: Annotation: Comments made about the product.
